column1: #Text=United States Senator Jeff Flake announces retirement , citing ' profoundly misguided ' party politics

#Text=Arizona Senator Jeff Flake announced on Tuesday he will not seek reelection when his term in the Senate is up next year , citing issues within the United States Republican Party and with President Donald Trump , whose behavior he called " reckless , outrageous , and undignified .

#Text= Based on the lack of support he has from the people of Arizona , [ retirement] 's probably a good move , " White House Press Secretary Sarah Huckabee Sanders told the media .

column1: #Text=Recent polls showed Flake has limited popularity with Republicans in Arizona .

#Text=Last year President Trump told other Arizona politicians he planned to personally spend US$ 10 million to see that Flake did not win the Republican primary , the intra-party election that names the party 's official candidate .

#Text=About two months ago Trump tweeted in support of Flake 's rival for the primary nod , Kelli Ward , " Great to see that Dr. Kelli Ward is running against Flake Jeff Flake , who is WEAK on borders , crime and a non-factor in Senate .
